Exercise:
Position the <h1> element 50px from the left, and 100px from the top, relative to the HTML page.

Answer:   position: absolute;
  left: 30px;
  top: 15px;
  
  <!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
.container {
  position: relative;
}

.topleft {
  position: absolute;
  left: 30px;
  top: 15px;
  font-size: 18px;
}

img {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  opacity: 0.3;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
  <img src="img_5terre.jpg" alt="Cinque Terre" width="1000" height="300">
  <div class="topleft">Top Left</div>
</div>

</body>
</html>

